2022 - wow were you a tough one. Challenging. Pushed me to my limits. To be totally honest, the hardest year yet for me. It taught me a lot about myself. I had some dark moments where I was feeling lost and unsure about a lot.
There was so much change. I moved. Got my little doggo, had to relocate studio spaces… it was a wild ride and was unsure as to why all of this was happening. 
Sometimes you can’t explain why things happen the way they did, you just have to trust the process and know it’s all meant to happen to teach you something. 
With all that said, I’m ending this year very happy and content and so grateful for what I have and everyone that’s in it. I just had my winter workshop with some of the most wonderful, amazing kids, and am kicking off registration for our tour next summer - @reflectiontheworkshop! 
I see the light at the end of the tunnel. 2022 was to show me my strength. 2023 is the year for me to win and all the hardwork to pay off. I feel it and I’m ready✨

thank you to every single person for all the texts, messages… anyone who reached out on my bday! i truly feel so grateful to start my year off reminded that I have the best, most supportive people around me. i don’t take any of it for granted ✨🫶🏼

A little recap of @reflectiontheworkshop 🫶🏼

I just want to thank each person who took part and helped me make this magical weekend come to life. 

Gia- for being there for literally anything & everything and stepping in as assistant aaand even part time photographer (; Couldn’t have done it without you baby girl. 

Abigail- for your talent, your heart and all the wisdom you shared with everyone. They were so lucky to learn from you. 

Jerel- thank you for capturing some of these moments. Appreciate you so much. 

Jess- for being YOU, being real & for always being there for me. You see things I don’t and tell it like it is! Thank you for giving them so much insight on real life events, and for that fire audition combo.

Mich- for sharing all your beauty tips & tricks! You are incredible. 

MaryAnn & Monika for letting me use your beautiful space! 

Andi- thank you for sweating it out in the heat with us for 2 hours and capturing such amazing photos. So happy they could all work with you. 

It takes a TEAM and I’m beyond grateful for mine. ✨
